The article discusses the signing of a continuing resolution to fund the government until early December. The author thanks both houses of Congress, particularly Senators Leahy and Shelby and Representatives DeLauro and Granger, for their bipartisan agreement that avoids a government shutdown. The funding addresses critical needs such as disaster relief for states impacted by Hurricane Ida and other natural disasters, as well as support for resettling Afghan allies and combating COVID-19 and the opioid crisis. The article emphasizes the importance of bipartisan work and the need for longer-term funding to serve the American people.